{
  "texts": [
    "This list follows the tables from [ACC + 19].",
    "It is worth noting that SEAL uses, by default, a centered binomial distribution for the generation of LWE samples.",
    "Microsoft's EVA [DKS + 20] is a compiler for homomorphic encryption built to work with the SEAL library.",
    "It contains a mechanism 26 to select an adequate decomposition of the ciphertext modulus depending on the desired application.",
    "24 The relevant code can be found in files bfvrns-parametergeneration.cpp, bgvrns-parametergeneration.cpp, and ckksrns-parametergeneration.cpp (Retrieved from OpenFHE v1.2.0)."
  ]
}